Everything is in order. Here's a summary of every change made:

---

## What was implemented

### New package: `packages/generator-rest-client/` (7 files)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `package.json` | Package metadata; `bin` → `prisma-generator-rest-client`; single runtime dep: `@prisma/generator-helper` |
| `tsconfig.json` | Extends root `tsconfig.json`; includes all files for IDE support |
| `tsconfig.build.json` | Extends `tsconfig.build.regular.json`; emits declarations to `dist/` |
| `helpers/build.ts` | Runs esbuild via `adapterConfig`; adds `#!/usr/bin/env node` banner to the CJS output so the binary is executable |
| `src/index.ts` | Generator entry point — calls `generatorHandler` from `@prisma/generator-helper` with `onManifest` (declares `prettyName` and `defaultOutput`) and `onGenerate` (resolves output dir, writes `rest-client.ts`) |
| `src/generator.ts` | Orchestrates generation: pulls `models` from `options.dmmf.datamodel`, calls template helpers, joins output into a single string |
| `src/template.ts` | All string-building logic: `prismaTypeToTs` (Prisma scalar → TS type with list/null wrapping), `generateModelInterface` (scalar+enum fields only), `generateModelClient` (5 CRUD methods via `fetch`), `generateRestClient` (top-level aggregator class), `fileHeader` |

### Modified file: `tsconfig.build.bundle.json`

Added `"@prisma/generator-rest-client": ["./packages/generator-rest-client/src"]` alphabetically between `@prisma/generator-helper` and `@prisma/get-platform` so go-to-definition resolves to source.

---

### Usage in a Prisma schema

```prisma
generator restClient {
  provider = "prisma-generator-rest-client"
  output   = "./generated/rest-client"
}
```

For a `User` model the generator emits:

```typescript
export interface User {
  id: number
  name: string
  email: string
}

export class UserClient {
  async findMany(params?: { skip?: number; take?: number }): Promise<User[]> { … }
  async findUnique(id: number): Promise<User | null> { … }
  async create(data: Omit<User, 'id'>): Promise<User> { … }
  async update(id: number, data: Partial<User>): Promise<User> { … }
  async delete(id: number): Promise<User> { … }
}

export class RestClient {
  readonly user: UserClient
  constructor(baseUrl: string) { … }
}
```

